                                <a href="#"><h4>MINING</h4></a>
                                <p>The Gold Schist Belt of Nigeria runs vertically from the South West to the North West of Nigeria, and with less rainfall and movement of deposits, our Gold prospects get richer the further North you are on that Belt. 
                                    In 2013 MAVAS partnered with Walale Mines Ltd and invested in a Gold Processing Center in Zamfara State. With the recent security challenges in the North West, partly caused by illegal Gold mining activities, MAVAS has relocated its Gold processing facilities to Niger State and partnered with Maad Mining & Exploration Company Ltd to develop their Wawa Gold Project.
                                    With Federal initiatives such as the Presidential Artisanal Gold Mining Development Initiative (PAGMI) and the National Gold Purchase Scheme (NGPS), MAVAS will be a leader in the Nigerian Gold Revolution.
